section.section:
The process described in subsection (a) of this section shall assess the quality of casework services through in-depth child and family case reviews that involve direct interviews by qualified and trained reviewers with:
children;
family members;
caseworkers;
judges;
court-appointed special advocates;
foster parents;
teachers;
medical personnel; and
others involved in providing support to the family.

The performance reviews shall determine whether:
the family participated in the development of the service agreement and the case plan;
the service agreement addressed the behaviors and circumstances that led to child abuse or neglect; and
the case plan and service agreement were timely initiated;
the case plan was implemented and progress was made;
all members of the team of professionals working with the family and the child met at regular intervals to make changes to services and supports as necessary;
a caseworker was promptly and regularly assigned and accessible to the case;
the assigned caseworker visited the child at least once per month; and
a supervisor has been regularly assigned and accessible to the case; and
the foster parent or kinship care provider is receiving all services necessary to meet the needs of the child, including child care, respite care, and other support services.
